==English==

===Etymology===
From the Latin term '[[volo]]', (I want) and '[[nolo]]', (I don't want). Originally, '''willy-nilly'''meant 'whether you want to or not', (e.g. You are going to the dentist's office to get your teeth pulled out willy-nilly!) although over time it evolved to describe something frivolous or care-free. (e.g. The pitching machine shot the baseballs everywhere, at any time, all willy-nilly.)

