====Definitions===
# {{idiom}} (adv.) Without regard for consequences or the will of those affected.
#:''So people chasing money churn out novels [[willy-nilly]]''.
#2. (adv.) Silly, or ridiculous (e.g. Alice in Wonderland describes a place where random things happen all willy nilly.)
#3. (adv.) Whether you want to or not (e.g. We are taking you to see the movie willy nilly.)

